<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-63-0585 </DOCNO><TEXT>A brief survey of the world trade and industry situation is followed byremarks on the status the national energy market holds within the internationaleconomy. The paper informs about the extent and scope of black coal subsidies,and describes particular aspects of the major coal markets, i.e. thesteel industry and the electric power industry. Final remarks are dedicatedto difficulties of adjustment.</TEXT></DOC>